The second sub-optimality can be removed by adopting a worldwide cap-and-trade system—so for each country, the optimal actual abatement (A
i) will be determined by where their marginal cost of abatement equals the global permit price (q)—while at the same time allowing countries to choose their own target abatement levels (T
i). To see how this works out, the resource constraint changes into3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
